# BusyBox config fragment – documentation of the MMU requirement for ESP32-S3
#
# NOTE: This fragment alone is NOT sufficient to fix the ash build error.
#       CONFIG_MMU is not a proper Kconfig symbol in BusyBox; syncconfig
#       strips it from the .config after merging fragments.  The actual fix
#       is in br2-external/external.mk, which redefines BUSYBOX_SET_MMU to
#       unconditionally disable CONFIG_NOMMU (the Buildroot FIXUP_CMDS step
#       that runs after syncconfig is the only mechanism that can reliably
#       set or clear NOMMU-related options).
#
# Root cause: jcmvbkbc fork's busybox.mk BUSYBOX_SET_MMU block is guarded by
# ifeq ($(BR2_USE_MMU),y).  BR2_USE_MMU is never propagated from auto.conf
# into Make in this fork.  The NOMMU else-branch fires: CONFIG_NOMMU is
# enabled, which sets BB_MMU=0 in BusyBox headers, causing ash to fail with:
#   shell/ash.c:308: #error "Do not even bother, ash will not run on NOMMU machine"
#
# This file is kept for documentation purposes and has no practical effect.
CONFIG_MMU=y
